OL,3,CToo costly to spend a penny? Councils
OL,4,Cclosing public loos as part of budget
OL,5,Ccuts
OL,7,FWoking Borough Council, for example,
OL,8,Fsays it has closed nearly all of its
OL,9,Fpublic toilets as part of measures to
OL,10,Fsave #8 million.
OL,12,FThe trend has sparked concerns from
OL,13,Fmembers of the public who have
OL,14,Fquestioned whether it is now too
OL,15,Fexpensive to spend a penny in their
OL,16,Flocal area.
