OL,3,CToo costly to spend a penny? Councils
OL,4,Cclosing public loos as part of budget
OL,5,Ccuts
OL,7,FSome community groups in an effort to
OL,8,Ftackle the issue themselves have
OL,9,Fdecided to take on the maintenance of
OL,10,Fpublic toilets in their area. For
OL,11,Fexample, in the Scottish town of
OL,12,FBiggar.
OL,14,FMike Chad, a member of the volunteer
OL,15,Fgroup in Biggar, told ITV News that
OL,16,Fthe group's formation had turned a
OL,17,Fmood of "anger and frustration" into
OL,18,Fone of "support and enthusiasm for
OL,19,Fthis new project".
